Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.03,0:00:22.58,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while, Flamme.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.02,0:00:44.06,Songs_OP2,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.12,0:00:57.04,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,You're there like the wind
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.04,0:01:01.66,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Closing your eyes at sunset
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.66,0:01:07.31,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what's on your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.58,0:01:12.63,Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(857,1)\blur0.25\fs35\fnGeorgia\fsp3.9\c&HFFFE65&\pos(328,254)\clip(109,253,547,294)\t(3943,4986,\clip(109,253,110,294))}Beyond Journey's End
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.03,0:01:16.01,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With your eyelids open
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.01,0:01:20.59,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyes shone like glass
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.59,0:01:27.36,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,It faintly smelled like a sunny day
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.29,0:01:38.49,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Clear up the sky, let flowers bloom
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.49,0:01:42.69,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Bloom and blame it on the sunny sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.69,0:01:47.08,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the rain, when it stops
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.08,0:01:52.08,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Will make you shine in the sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.08,0:01:57.48,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Calm the stirring sounds in my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.48,0:02:01.52,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,We go like the sunny wind
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.52,0:02:05.93,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Go on and fly over that cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.93,0:02:10.76,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Further and further away
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.98,0:02:16.99,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(388,269.5)}Episode 21: The World of Magic
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.44,0:02:22.96,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Bargland.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.32,0:02:46.50,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,The young are too hot-blooded.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.96,0:02:50.13,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,The so-called privilege is nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.32,0:02:53.88,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What makes you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.39,0:02:56.93,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you even have to ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.69,0:03:03.03,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,The greatest joy of magic \Nlies in searching for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.91,0:03:05.55,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.07,0:03:07.04,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.53,0:03:12.71,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Time passes quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.43,0:03:17.79,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,The student I chose to train on a whim \Nhas already returned with her own student.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.38,0:03:19.67,Flashback,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,This is Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.77,0:03:21.91,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,An elf, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.84,0:03:25.43,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,She's strong. I like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.41,0:03:29.83,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me what spell you desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.83,0:03:31.63,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I shall grant you just one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.98,0:03:34.57,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,A spell that I desire?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.09,0:03:40.50,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I have knowledge of nearly every grimoire \Nthat's ever been written.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.44,0:03:47.71,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Mages spend their entire lives \Nsearching for the spell they desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.26,0:03:51.34,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me what yours is, \Nand I shall grant it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.31,0:03:53.33,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.74,0:03:59.70,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The greatest joy of magic \Nlies in searching for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.24,0:04:05.05,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Flamme, this girl is no good after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.40,0:04:09.12,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,She lacks a burning ambition.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.76,0:04:14.58,Flashback,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,Master, someday this girl \Nwill defeat the Demon King.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.12,0:04:20.54,Flashback,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,It will be a mage like her \Nwho clears the way to a peaceful era.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.23,0:04:23.54,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying I cannot?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.54,0:04:27.53,Flashback,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,As one who seeks battle, \Nyou cannot kill the Demon King.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.14,0:04:30.23,Flashback,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,We can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.77,0:04:37.89,Flashback,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you can't imagine yourself \Nliving in a peaceful era, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.07,0:04:44.42,Flashback,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren is a mage of a peaceful era.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.18,0:04:52.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Good answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.02,0:04:55.47,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This is how mages ought to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.14,0:05:12.71,DefaultItalics,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. He won't freeze at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.13,0:05:15.19,DefaultItalics,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,The difference between \Nour mana is too great.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.78,0:05:16.96,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Nephtear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.99,0:05:26.61,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.23,0:05:31.27,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Kanne, defense!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.27,0:05:32.14,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.45,0:05:37.92,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,You two put on quite the show earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.31,0:05:41.24,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,so I believe I know most of your tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.84,0:05:48.16,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Relatively non-lethal ice magic,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.50,0:05:51.19,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,and a mage who can't fight without water.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.65,0:05:55.91,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,What am I even doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.43,0:05:58.91,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,This really is just babysitting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.35,0:06:07.17,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,That's not a nice thing to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.45,0:06:12.59,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Won't you run out of mana \Ncasting such flashy spells?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.47,0:06:16.22,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,You graduated from magic school, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.62,0:06:22.67,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Are the old folks still teaching their students\Nto fight defensive battles of attrition?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.00,0:06:24.32,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.88,0:06:27.90,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Let me lecture you on the history of magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.31,0:06:36.91,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,The defensive spell developed to combat \NZoltraak is highly resistant to magic itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.91,0:06:41.92,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,but its effectiveness against physical \Nobjects has hardly changed since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.38,0:06:45.32,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, there's a clear reason for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.47,0:06:52.17,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,It's enough to defend against the physical \Nattacks of monsters and warriors.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.79,0:06:56.14,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Defensive magic mustn't be over-engineered.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.65,0:06:59.81,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,If we aimed for perfection, \Nthe technique would become too complex,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.21,0:07:03.19,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,which would have a fatal effect \Non activation time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.79,0:07:07.33,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,The history of magic is one \Nof attacking and defending.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.33,0:07:09.88,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,It's the reason there's a trend \Nfor modern attack spells
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.88,0:07:12.19,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,to involve controlling physical objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.12,0:07:16.16,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand what I'm getting at?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.46,0:07:20.55,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Kanne, no! Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.42,0:07:32.38,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,My spells overwhelm my opponents \Nwith high-volume physical attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.81,0:07:35.59,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Now stay down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.10,0:07:41.14,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.14,0:07:42.94,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not interested in hurting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.53,0:07:46.82,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Or do you want me to kill you after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.69,0:07:50.81,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Should you be approaching us so carelessly?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.17,0:07:54.57,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Sixty percent of the human body \Nis made of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.00,0:07:56.57,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.37,0:08:00.07,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Magic is a world of visual imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.51,0:08:04.60,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Can you picture how that water is distributed\Nthroughout a person's body,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.09,0:08:07.62,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,and how you'd remove and manipulate it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.03,0:08:12.78,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,How would you do that to a mage \Nprotected by a large amount of mana?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.09,0:08:17.34,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Spells can't produce effects \Nyou can't picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.58,0:08:23.35,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,And even if there were water here, \Na small girl like you is no threat to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.02,0:08:28.06,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Not even bluffing works? \NI hate adults like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.26,0:08:31.73,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,But I have figured out one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.03,0:08:34.75,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,You're lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.54,0:08:38.55,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,If you loved fighting enough \Nto lecture us on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.55,0:08:41.88,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,you would've beaten us \Nsomewhere there was water.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.49,0:08:44.57,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,What are you so afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.37,0:08:50.14,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Behave yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.39,0:08:54.63,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,My job is just to put you two to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.23,0:08:57.50,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,As long as Denken doesn't lose, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.91,0:09:14.54,DefaultItalics,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, this battle will end \Nwhen she exhausts my mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.16,0:09:18.87,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,This is all a bit tough for this old body.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.17,0:09:23.35,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies, Frieren, but I'm \Ngoing to settle this quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.74,0:09:27.38,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Waldgose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.40,0:09:30.88,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Daosdorg.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.40,0:09:41.13,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,What is that decrepit old man doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.03,0:09:45.14,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,That old man fights rather spectacularly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.14,0:09:47.35,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Will the barrier hold?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.35,0:09:52.89,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. The barrier was created \Nby the great mage Serie.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.30,0:09:56.35,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,It cannot be destroyed by brute force.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.35,0:09:58.94,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? That's good, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.53,0:10:02.03,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, since around yesterday evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.03,0:10:04.89,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,someone's been analyzing the barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.63,0:10:07.13,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.13,0:10:08.05,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.93,0:10:11.49,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, they're wasting their time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.15,0:10:15.79,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think there's a mage \Nin this world greater than Serie?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.68,0:10:26.65,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Catastravia.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.39,0:10:37.82,DefaultItalics,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible. A counterattack?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.82,0:10:40.29,DefaultItalics,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,That was a continuous volley \Nof spears of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.29,0:10:41.90,DefaultItalics,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,She shouldn't have had the opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.06,0:11:03.05,DefaultItalics,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm out of mana. So this is the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.45,0:11:05.05,DefaultItalics,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.05,0:11:09.80,DefaultItalics,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,She only used basic combat \Nspells until the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.44,0:11:15.89,DefaultItalics,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,This was practically a combat \Nlesson for a trainee mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.72,0:11:18.16,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.72,0:11:22.56,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Even at my level, there was \Nstill someone above me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.56,0:11:24.63,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me where Laufen is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.07,0:11:26.80,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I know you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.18,0:11:29.13,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm taking back our Stille.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.11,0:11:33.99,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,If you were in my position, \Ndo you think you'd tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.86,0:11:36.07,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.37,0:11:49.84,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Laufen, you're hiding nearby, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.12,0:11:52.36,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Bring the Stille here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.46,0:11:56.45,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't, I'll kill Denken.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.07,0:12:00.85,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do it, Laufen. \NShe doesn't intend to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.29,0:12:02.57,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.57,0:12:04.47,DefaultItalics,LAUREN,0000,0000,0000,,The old man was beaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.47,0:12:09.86,DefaultItalics,LAUREN,0000,0000,0000,,She's a far better mage than me—\Nno, better than even Richter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.43,0:12:12.24,DefaultItalics,LAUREN,0000,0000,0000,,But she underestimates us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.24,0:12:14.41,DefaultItalics,LAUREN,0000,0000,0000,,She's not touching the old man's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.68,0:12:19.18,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't use Jilwer. Stay hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.41,0:12:22.82,Default,DENEKN,0000,0000,0000,,If you release even the slightest bit \Nof mana, she'll detect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.82,0:12:26.39,DefaultItalics,LAUREN,0000,0000,0000,,From this distance, I could \Nretrieve the old man and flee!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.39,0:12:28.41,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't. It's a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.41,0:12:30.17,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You leave me no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.17,0:12:32.98,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really want to do this, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.20,0:12:36.43,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Found you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.75,0:12:40.31,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,You fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.56,0:12:45.46,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,You inexperienced fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.46,0:12:48.96,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,You knew she wouldn't kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.96,0:12:54.00,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,But she planned to hurt you \Nwithout killing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.34,0:12:57.59,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,We still would've won.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.95,0:13:03.33,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so desperate \Nto become a first-class mage?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.33,0:13:07.47,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,You've got wealth, influence, \Nand everything else you could want.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.69,0:13:16.68,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,My homeland is located deep \Nin the Northern Plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.25,0:13:22.86,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Because the demons are acting up, only \Nfirst-class mages can enter the area now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.71,0:13:27.13,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to visit a grave \NI haven't been to in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.13,0:13:28.65,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.00,0:13:33.38,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't you go help the kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.35,0:13:37.76,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it's too late, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.76,0:13:42.46,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Richter will kill them before he faces you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.92,0:13:46.76,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,He's capable of making pragmatic choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.76,0:13:50.35,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,They'll be fine. Kanne and Lawine will win.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.48,0:13:55.37,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I just finished analyzing the barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.69,0:14:00.28,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't expecting Denken to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.20,0:14:02.36,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.02,0:14:06.14,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Babysitting time is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.64,0:14:34.31,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,He's actually trying to kill us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.66,0:14:36.83,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,We won't last a minute against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.96,0:14:40.05,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,Analyzing the barrier?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.43,0:14:41.90,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.99,0:14:48.83,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren. Don't tell me, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.13,0:14:59.13,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,Genau.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.94,0:15:02.95,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a problem. It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.56,0:15:05.77,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the world were turned upside down—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.24,0:15:14.23,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to break.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.35,0:15:25.98,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,Sense, who is that elf mage?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.67,0:15:30.49,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,According to the list of test-takers, \Nher name is Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.81,0:15:33.74,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,That's the name of the mage who \Ntraveled with the party of heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.33,0:15:37.80,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,She apparently had a holy emblem, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.37,0:15:41.17,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,So she's the last great mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.95,0:15:43.96,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Now you've done it, Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.46,0:15:48.40,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a thousand years, \Nand this is how you say hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.63,0:15:52.49,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,This is why I can't quit being a mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.98,0:15:57.35,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,In the world of magic, sometimes \Nthe world is turned upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.41,0:16:01.89,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe you actually \Ndestroyed the barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.24,0:16:04.28,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.28,0:16:06.66,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Because I felt sorry for Kanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.09,0:16:09.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Magic should be free.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.84,0:16:12.92,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,She controls water, does she?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.45,0:16:15.61,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Magic is a world of visual imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.27,0:16:20.61,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Can you imagine defeating a mage \Nwho controls water in the rain?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.44,0:16:23.61,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.55,0:16:27.00,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt Richter can either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.44,0:16:28.76,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,The barrier...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.65,0:16:31.41,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.41,0:16:32.25,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,It's raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.99,0:16:35.57,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,No, I can figure out what happened later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.14,0:16:37.50,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,I have to finish them now—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.24,0:16:40.40,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,You finally showed an opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.83,0:16:43.01,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Your panic is disrupting your mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.01,0:16:45.10,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,This will only buy you time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.91,0:16:53.78,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,I see now why you feared a spell \Nthat could control water.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.66,0:17:00.53,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,This is the perfect example of the \Nhigh-volume physical attacks you mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.90,0:17:04.28,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Lawine, don't let him get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.77,0:17:06.42,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Reamstroha.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.33,0:17:11.92,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,There's nowhere for me to run, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.70,0:17:17.09,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,This is why I don't like water.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.29,0:17:32.91,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you won.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.40,0:17:35.20,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get away from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.61,0:17:37.70,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The sun sets in two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.70,0:17:39.70,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You can conceal your mana \Nuntil then, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.70,0:17:42.45,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any mana left to conceal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.85,0:17:45.03,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You did well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.05,0:17:47.17,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Don't pat my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.92,0:17:51.92,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.40,0:17:55.13,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It was inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.34,0:18:03.03,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Denken and I are out of mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.30,0:18:07.34,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,We have two hours left.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.34,0:18:09.09,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,We're finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.30,0:18:15.05,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Laufen, can you dispel the binding?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.05,0:18:18.90,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,You must be joking. \NThis binding spell is ridiculously powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.70,0:18:22.78,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Then bring down the tree instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.22,0:18:33.39,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Denken, there's nothing we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.99,0:18:38.29,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have the mana left \Nto use Jilwer anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.04,0:18:45.56,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Richter and Laufen, what do you think \Nan imperial mage does in this situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.62,0:18:49.55,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,He keeps fighting until the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.15,0:18:55.56,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll search for signs of battles fought \Nby other parties and track them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.15,0:18:58.81,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Fern,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.25,0:19:01.87,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,you're really rather boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.90,0:19:07.09,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,You seriously do only cast basic spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.09,0:19:09.76,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You should direct your \Ncomplaints to Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.93,0:19:14.62,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, \Nthat elf is your master, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.28,0:19:20.53,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,It's her fault we're soaking wet right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.53,0:19:22.62,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you give her an earful, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.39,0:19:24.97,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I intend to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.98,0:19:29.82,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Also, she doesn't limit what spells \NI cast outside of combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.47,0:19:34.12,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, you did cast \Na spell to catch that bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.65,0:19:36.82,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,What other spells can you use?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.37,0:19:38.91,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.34,0:19:41.93,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I have a spell that lets you \Nsee through clothes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.28,0:19:44.65,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going to cast it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.41,0:19:49.32,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to interrupt your \Npleasant conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.32,0:19:52.47,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,but maybe you shouldn't reveal \Ntoo many of your tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.79,0:19:56.75,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,From the second test onward, \Nwe'll be competing against one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.46,0:20:00.09,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.29,0:20:01.60,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry 'bout that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.41,0:20:06.59,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,But I think you should've opened up \Nsome more, four-eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.38,0:20:12.77,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,There they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.77,0:20:14.68,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a defeated party.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.22,0:20:18.80,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,The corpse of one of their \Nmembers was nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.80,0:20:24.53,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Even though there's no way for them to pass, \Nthey're keeping a tight hold on their Stille.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.55,0:20:31.24,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Are we going to negotiate with them, Denken?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.24,0:20:32.96,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,They wouldn't cooperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.96,0:20:37.67,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,If I were in their position, \NI'd refuse even money.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.10,0:20:39.08,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.50,0:20:42.04,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't sit right with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.04,0:20:44.22,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not about logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.66,0:20:47.96,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Laufen, wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.96,0:20:50.19,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,If you see an opportunity, \Ntake their Stille.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.19,0:20:52.14,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Richter, come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.23,0:20:54.66,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,What do you intend to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.56,0:21:07.88,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,We're approaching them head-on?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.88,0:21:10.24,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have any mana left.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.56,0:21:13.45,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.81,0:21:17.95,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,They're in the same boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.01,0:21:27.75,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.95,0:21:33.89,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,You're a man, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.32,0:21:36.97,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,You're joking, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.71,0:21:43.87,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's settle this with our fists!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.39,0:22:11.72,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,It's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.46,0:22:17.40,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,The first test is now over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.13,0:22:22.27,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,Six parties—eighteen individuals—\Nhave passed the first test.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.70,0:22:24.77,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,The second test will take place \Nthree days from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.13,0:22:27.85,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,You will be informed of the details later.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.84,0:22:31.05,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,That's all. You are dismissed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.04,0:22:37.53,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It's been two days since \Nthey left for the exam.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.19,0:22:42.53,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I can stay up as late as I want, \Nand Fern isn't around to get mad at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.53,0:22:44.88,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so happy, it's scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.47,0:22:48.81,Default,BARTENDER,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like you've got it rough, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.04,0:22:53.18,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm alright (I'll be alright)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.18,0:22:56.10,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I hear you (I care about you)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.10,0:23:01.68,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The wind teases this hair that's longer now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.68,0:23:04.12,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,There's meaning in everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.62,0:23:07.10,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the days that came to a halt
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.70,0:23:13.74,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I finally understand,\NI've caught up to you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.74,0:23:17.53,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,See, things that couldn't have been
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.53,0:23:20.43,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Seen if it weren't for these eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.43,0:23:25.10,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Why? They begin to overflow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.10,0:23:31.33,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I won't ask to see you, so at least
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.33,0:23:37.12,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Let me remember the past, just for today
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.12,0:23:43.13,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if we were to meet again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.13,0:23:49.01,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,No more hesitations, I'd choose the present
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.07,0:23:53.03,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Anytime, anywhere, yah (wherever you are)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.03,0:23:57.68,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Anytime, anywhere (smile for me)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.68,0:24:00.66,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be there (close your eyes,\Nand I'll always be there)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.66,0:24:03.41,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even if there are no absolutes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.41,0:24:06.48,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'm always aware of your thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.48,0:24:12.51,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Those tears will be alright,\Ndawn will surely break
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.96,0:24:19.42,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'm whispering our lullaby\Nfor you to come back home
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.08,0:24:21.22,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sharing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.66,0:24:22.98,DefaultTop,LECKER,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.02,0:24:22.98,DefaultOverlapTop,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.65,0:24:26.02,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,You're even more spoiled than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.00,0:24:26.04,DefaultTop,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not my birthday. \NCan I really indulge myself like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.78,0:24:26.04,DefaultOverlap,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,You must eat your vegetables, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.04,0:24:27.94,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,She's such a pain in the butt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.26,0:24:27.95,DefaultOverlap,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,We're no longer a party.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.57,0:24:30.02,Signs_NextEp,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(229,1)\blur3\t(20,312,\blur0.2)\pos(320,113.5)\c&H000000&\t(312,646,\c&HF6F6F6&)\fsp1.6\t(\fsp1)}Episode 22\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NFuture Enemies
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.95,0:24:30.09,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, we'll be enemies.